File Naming:
All header files are writtern in lowercase.
Example:device.h,room.h,smartHome.h
Source files use the same names as header files.
Example:device.cpp,room.cpp,smartHome.cpp

Class Naming:
Class names start with a capital letter.
Each word in class name starts with capital(PascalCase)
Example:Device, Room, SmartHome, Light, Fan, AC.

Variable Naming:
Variables are written in camelCase.
First letter is small, next words start with capital.
Example: deviceCount, roomName, speed, temperature

Function Naming:
Function names are also written in camelCase.
Example: turnOn(), turnOff(), showStatus(), addDevice()

Constant Naming:
Constants are written in uppercase letters.
Example:MAX_DEVICES, MAX_ROOMS

Object Naming:
Object names are kept small and meaningful.
Example:living, bedroom, kitchen, home

General Rules:
Meaningful and simple names are used.
Same naming style is followed throughout the project.
No unnecessary complex names are used.
Code readibility is maintained.
